Reasoning: The paper discusses the evolution of Web and service technologies, as well as current trends in cloud computing, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is likely the most relevant sub-category, as the paper focuses on the communication aspect of interaction between software components, which is a key concern in distributed computing. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant, as the paper discusses software implementations applicable in clouds. cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper discusses architectures and protocols for interaction between loosely coupled components, which are relevant to distributed systems and control. Finally, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible sub-category, as the paper discusses transport mechanisms and emerging client-to-client communication capabilities in Web clients, which are relevant to networking and Internet architecture.
